roadcasting that the coalition will sacrifice large-scale coordination and the welfare of distant or digital beings to remain comfortable within existing moral sensibilities. That is a form of moral conservatism tied to local preferences, not to a deeper cooperative principle. In a universe of diverse rational agents, such a stance is harder to justify under a veil-of-ignorance test and is less likely to be part of a robustly stable cosmic contract."
